If an admin for Piratesbay did something to ban the address in the range of 64.125.152.xxx and 64.125.154.xxx, you didn't do us any favors. His were the only seeds at 100%.

Last night there must have been close to 50 clients in those address ranges. Now there is only us 95.9%ers left. I had hoped that a few of us would get 100% then I would have done a "kick and ban" on his addresses. Now if he doesn't come back or someone with a 100% starts to seed we are all dead in the water. The NTI pirates didn't have any 100% this morning either, but I just looked and there were 2 at 100%, but not for this one.

Two scenarios I can think of that one would do this for, so many clients in the same holdings of addresses with such low upload speeds, would be if a film's owners wanted to sabotage the torrent, or if someone wanted to repackage the torrent then repost it in their own account while killing the original torrent.
